'''美国诉黄金德案'''（{{lang-en|United States v. Wong Kim Ark}}）{{scite|169|649|1898}}，是一起[[美国联邦最高法院|美国联邦最高法院]]判决所有美国境內[[出生|出生]]者都是[[美国公民|美国公民]]的里程碑式案例。判决在解读[[美利坚合众国宪法第十四条修正案|美利坚合众国宪法第十四条修正案]]的{{link-en|公民权条款|Citizenship Clause}}上建立了重要的[[判决先例|判决先例]]。

黄金德于1871年出生于[[旧金山|旧金山]]，他的父母都是华人。一次出国旅行归来时，移民局根据1882年5月6日通过的《[[排华法案|排华法案]]》拒绝他入境。黄金德为此将政府告上法庭，挑战政府拒绝承认其公民身份的做法。联邦最高法院在判决中支持了他的意见，认定根据第十四条修正案，每一位在美国出生的人都是美国公民，即使他父母是外国人亦不例外，并且这样的特权即使有联邦国会通过的法律也不能剥夺。

此案件特别突出了对公民公款中一个短语准确含义理解的分歧，即一个在美国出生的人是否符合“并受其管辖”的要求从而获得公民权。最高法院的多数意见总结认为这一短语的意思是受到美国法律的管辖。在这一基础上，第十四条修正案将被解读为赋予几乎任何在美国领土出生的人美国公民身份（即[[属地主义|属地主义]]原则）。而法院对此持不同意见的两位法官则认为“并受其管辖”应该是从政治上效忠于美国，即根据[[血统主义|血统主义]]（即[[属人主义|属人主义]]）原则，新生儿的国籍将根据其父母的国籍来认定<ref name="Wong_Kim_Ark_715">''United States v. Wong Kim Ark'', {{ussc|169|649|1898|pin=715}}.</ref>。

研究人员在2007年的一篇对黄金德案后相关判决的法律分析文章中认为，以属地主义原则赋予公民权的概念“从来没有被最高法院严肃地质疑过，并且也由下级法院作为教条所接受”<ref name="Glen" />{{rp|80}}。2010年的一篇针对公民权条款历史的评论文章指出，黄金德案判决使公民权条款“适用于在美国领土上出生的外国人士后代”，并指出最高法院“自‘非法移民’一词出现以来还从未重新审视过这一判决”<ref name="Epps">{{cite journal | last=Epps |first=Garrett |title=The Citizenship Clause: A 'Legislative History' | journal=American University Law Review | volume=60 | issue=2 | pages=329–388 | year=2010 | archivedate=2013-01-12 | deadurl=no | format = [[pdf|pdf]] | archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20130112212712/http://digitalcommons.wcl.american.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1607&context=aulr |url=http://digitalcommons.wcl.american.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1607&context=aulr | accessdate=2013-12-09}}</ref>{{rp|332}}。

不过自1990年代起，长期存在的非法移民后代也能自动获得公民权这一做法随着流入美国移民数量的大量增加而引起了不少争议。法律学者表示不认同将黄金德案的判决先例应用到非法移民后代身上。国会曾先后几次试图对属地主义原则作出限制，或是通过法案来重新定义“管辖”一词，又或试图通过一条宪法修正案来推翻判决，但这些努力都没有成功。

== 背景 ==
=== 早期的美国公民权法律 ===
{{see also|美国公民出生地原则}}
美国[[公民|公民权]]相关法律是以两个传统原则建立的：一个是“[[属地主义|属地主义]]”原则，也称“[[普通法|普通法]]主义”原则；另一个是“[[血统主义|血统主义]]”原则，亦称“{{link-en|国际公法 (公法)|Public international law|国际公法}}”原则或是“国际主义”原则。根据属地主义原则或英国的普通法，一位新生儿的国籍将按其出生地来判断，无须考虑新生儿政治上是否向该国效忠或是其父母的相应情况。而在血统主义原则或国际公法原则下，新生儿的国籍将与其父母（主要是与父亲，除非是[[非婚生子女|未婚生育]]才会与母亲）保持一致，不考虑出生地<ref name="Woodworth1896">{{cite journal | author=Woodworth, Marshall B. | journal=American Law Review | volume=30 | pages=535–555 | year=1896 | publisher=Review Pub. Company | location=St. Louis | title=Citizenship of the United States under the Fourteenth Amendment}}</ref>{{rp|536}}<ref name="7fam1111a">"Acquisition of U.S. Citizenship by Birth in the United States", 7 FAM 1111(a).</ref>。

纵观美国历史，虽然直至[[美国内战|内战]]结束后才有对公民权作出明确定义的法律<ref>Woodworth (1896), p. 538.  "As a matter of fact, there was no definition in the constitution, or in any of the Acts of Congress, as to what constituted citizenship, until the enactment of the Civil Rights Bill in 1866, and the adoption of the Fourteenth Amendment in 1868."</ref>，但以属地主义原则判断公民身份一直是占有主导地位的法律原则，而且此做法已经得到普遍接受<ref>Woodworth (1896), p. 538.  "So generally accepted and acted upon has been the impression that birth in this country ''ipso facto'' confers citizenship, that there are, to-day, thousands of persons born in the United States of foreign parents, who consider themselves, and are recognized, legally, as citizens.  Among these are very many voters, whose right to vote, because born here of foreign parents, has never been seriously questioned."</ref><ref>"Authorities", 7 FAM 1119(d).  "Until 1866, the citizenship status of persons born in the United States was not defined in the Constitution or in any federal statute.  Under the common law rule of '''jus soli'''—the law of the soil—persons born in the United States generally acquired U.S. citizenship at birth."</ref>，故所有在美国领土出生的新生儿都将自动获得公民权。唯一例外则是在内战前[[美国奴隶制度|奴隶]]遭排除在外，因為他们被认为是奴隶主的财产，因而不能成为美国公民<ref>Woodworth (1896), p. 537.  "[T]he commonly accepted notion in this country, both prior and subsequent to the adoption of the Fourteenth Amendment ... has been that birth within the United States, although of alien parents, was sufficient, of itself, to confer the right of citizenship, without any other requisite, such for instance, as the naturalization proceedings which take place with reference to aliens."</ref><ref>{{cite web |author =Walter Dellinger, Assistant Attorney General |title =Legislation denying citizenship at birth to certain children born in the United States |work =Memoranda and Opinions |publisher =Office of Legal Counsel, U.S. Department of Justice |date =1995-12-13 |url =http://www.justice.gov/olc/deny.tes.31.htm |quote =A bill that would deny citizenship to children born in the United States to certain classes of alien parents is unconstitutional on its face. A constitutional amendment to restrict birthright citizenship, although not technically unlawful, would flatly contradict the Nation's constitutional history and constitutional traditions. |postscript =<!-- intentionally blank to work around a bug in the template --> |accessdate =2013-12-09 |deadurl =yes |archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20131222230830/http://www.justice.gov/olc/deny.tes.31.htm |archivedate =2013-12-22 }}</ref><ref>''Lynch v. Clarke'', 3 N.Y.Leg.Obs. 236 (N.Y. 1844).</ref>。1844年[[纽约州|纽约州]]有过一个以属地主义原则判定公民权的典型案例[[林奇诉克拉克案|林奇诉克拉克案]]（Lynch v. Clarke），案中一对外国夫妇侨居在[[纽约市|纽约市]]时生下了一名女婴，这个女婴就由法官根据属地主义原则判定是一位美国公民<ref>''Lynch v. Clarke'', 3 N.Y.Leg.Obs. at 250.  "Upon principle, therefore, I can entertain no doubt, but that by the law of the United States, every person born within the dominions and allegiance of the United States, whatever were the situation of his parents, is a natural born citizen....  I am bound to say that the general understanding ... is that birth in this country does of itself constitute citizenship....  Thus when at an election, the inquiry is made whether a person offering to vote is a citizen or an alien, if he answers that he is a native of this country, it is received as conclusive that he is a citizen....  The universality of the public sentiment in this instance ... indicates the strength and depth of the common law principle, and confirms the position that the adoption of the Federal Constitution wrought no change in that principle."</ref>。

美国公民权同样也可以通过血统主义原则获得，国会曾通过《{{link-en|1790年入籍法|Naturalization Act of 1790}}》确认了这一原则，主要是为了让身在国外美国公民的孩子也可以自动拥有公民权<ref name="Nat_Act_1790">{{cite web |url=http://rs6.loc.gov/cgi-bin/ampage?collId=llsl&fileName=001/llsl001.db&recNum=227 |title=An Act to establish an ''<nowiki>[sic]</nowiki>'' uniform Rule of Naturalization 1st Cong., Sess. II, Chap. 3; 1 Stat. 103. 1790-3-26	 |publisher=The Library of Congress |quote=''Be it enacted'' ... That any alien, being a free white person, who shall have resided within the limits and under the jurisdiction of the United States for the term of two years, may be admitted to become a citizen thereof....  And the children of citizens of the United States, that may be born beyond sea, or out of the limits of the United States, shall be considered as natural born citizens: ''Provided,'' That the right of citizenship shall not descend to persons whose fathers have never been resident in the United States.... |accessdate=2013-12-09}}</ref>。此外，移民美国的外国人也可以通过[[归化|归化]]程序成为美国公民，这一过程起初只限定对“自由的白人”开放，但之后已经废除了限制<ref name="Nat_Act_1790" />。

来自非洲的黑奴曾被长期排除在美国公民以外。1857年，联邦最高法院对[[斯科特诉桑福德案|斯科特诉桑福德案]]作出判决<ref>''Dred Scott v. Sandford'', {{ussc|60|393|1857}}.</ref>，认为根据宪法，所有奴隶或之前曾是奴隶的人以及他们的后代都不能成为美国公民<ref>{{cite journal | url=http://www.americanheritage.com/content/1857-dred-scott-decision | title=The Dred Scott Decision | author=Schwarz, Frederic D. | journal=American Heritage | year=2007-02-03 | volume=58 | issue=1 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20120614110348/http://www.americanheritage.com/content/1857-dred-scott-decision  |publisher=American Heritage Publishing | location=Rockville, MD | accessdate=2012-06-14 |archivedate=2012-06-14 |deadurl=no}}</ref>。此外，由于[[美洲原住民|印第安人]]部落和該[[保留地|保留地]]一度不属于联邦政府的管辖范围，因此[[美洲原住民|美洲原住民]]起初亦不獲納入美国公民之列。

=== 第十四条修正案公民权条款 ===
{{main|美利坚合众国宪法第十四条修正案}}
内战结束后，奴隶制被全面废除，国会颁布了《{{link-en|1866年民权法案|Civil Rights Act of 1866}}》<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.milestonedocuments.com/documents/view/civil-rights-act-of-1866 |title=An Act to protect all Persons in the United States in their Civil Rights, and furnish the Means of their Vindication |publisher=39th Cong., Sess. I, Chap. 31; 14 Stat. 27.  April 9, 1866 |accessdate=2013-12-09 |work=Milestone Documents |archivedate=2013-12-03 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203055256/http://www.milestonedocuments.com/documents/view/civil-rights-act-of-1866}}</ref><ref>"Authorities", 7 FAM 1119(e).  "This rule was made part of the Civil Rights Act of April 9, 1866 (14 Statutes at Large 27)...."</ref>。其中明确规定包括获得解放的奴隶在内，“除了未被征税的印第安人以外，所有在美国出生且非任何外国势力的人”都是美国公民<ref>{{cite web|work=The Online Library of Liberty |archivedate=2013-05-20 |url=http://oll.libertyfund.org/?option=com_staticxt&staticfile=show.php%3Ftitle=2282&chapter=216253&layout=html&Itemid=27 |title=Civil Rights Act of 1866 |accessdate=2013-12-09 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130520094210/http://oll.libertyfund.org/?option=com_staticxt&staticfile=show.php%3Ftitle%3D2282&chapter=216253&layout=html&Itemid=27 }}</ref>。

由于担心《1866年民权法案》中保证的公民权遭将来的国会立法废除<ref name="Congress_might_repeal_1866">''Wong Kim Ark'', 169 U.S. at 675.  "The same Congress, shortly afterwards, evidently thinking it unwise, and perhaps unsafe, to leave so important a declaration of rights to depend upon an ordinary act of legislation, which might be repealed by any subsequent Congress, framed the Fourteenth Amendment of the Constitution...."</ref>，或是被法院判定违宪<ref name="Democracy_Reborn">{{cite book | title=Democracy Reborn: The Fourteenth Amendment and the Fight for Equal Rights in Post-Civil War America | author=Epps, Garrett | publisher=Holt Paperbacks | year=2007 | isbn=978-0-8050-8663-8 | page=174 | quote=The opposition made several arguments.  The citizenship provision was unconstitutional, they contended, and would grant citizenship, not only to freed slaves, but to Indians living off their reservations, to Chinese born in the United States, and even to gypsies.  [Illinois Senator Lyman] Trumbull agreed that it would, opening a chorus of cries that the bill would cede California to China and make America a mongrel nation. | postscript= <!-- intentionally blank to work around a bug in the template --> }}</ref><ref name="Congress_cannot_make_a_citizen">{{cite web |title=The Congressional Globe 39th Cong., 1st Sess. 597 |url=http://memory.loc.gov/cgi-bin/ampage?collId=llcg&fileName=070/llcg070.db&recNum=702 |date=1866-02-02 |quote=Congress has no power to make a citizen.... [only] to establish a uniform rule of naturalization. |accessdate=2013-12-09}}</ref>，法案通过后国会马上就起草了美利坚合众国宪法第十四条修正案并递交各州批准（整个过程都在1868年完成）<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.loc.gov/law/help/citizenship/fourteenth_amendment_citizenship.php | title=Law Library of Congress: Fourteenth Amendment and Citizenship | publisher=Library of Congress | accessdate=2013-12-09 | quote=However, because there were concerns that the Civil Rights Act might be subsequently repealed or limited the Congress took steps to include similar language when it considered the draft of the Fourteenth Amendment. | postscript= <!-- intentionally blank to work around a bug in the template --> |archivedate=2013-03-03 |deadurl=no |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20130303132701/http://www.loc.gov/law/help/citizenship/fourteenth_amendment_citizenship.php}}</ref>。第十四条修正案中的许多规定确立了对公民身份的宪法保证：“所有在合众国出生或归化合众国并受其管辖的人，都是合众国的和他们居住州的公民”<ref>{{cite book |title=美国宪政历程：影响美国的25个司法大案 |author1=任东来 |author2=陈伟 |author3=白雪峰 |author4=Charles J. McClain |author5=Laurene Wu McClain |publisher=中国法制出版社 |isbn=7-80182-138-6 |page=574|date=2004年1月}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |author=李道揆 |title=美国政府和政治（下册）|publisher=商务印书馆 |year=1999 |pages=775-799}}</ref><ref>{{cite book | first=Frederic Jesup | last=Stimson | url=http://books.google.com/books?id=veDMy4aUwIgC&pg=PA76&lpg=PA76 | title=The Law of the Federal and State Constitutions of the United States | publisher=The Lawbook Exchange | location=Clark, NJ | year=2004 | page=76 | isbn=978-1-58477-369-6 }}</ref>。这一公民权条款由来自[[密歇根州|密歇根州]]的[[联邦参议员|联邦参议员]]{{link-en|雅各布·M·霍华德|Jacob M. Howard}}于1866年5月30日提出，是对众议院联席决议起草的第十四条修正案初稿的一个补充<ref name="Cong_Globe_2890">''Cong. Globe,'' 39th Cong., 1st Sess. [http://memory.loc.gov/cgi-bin/ampage?collId=llcg&fileName=073/llcg073.db&recNum=11 2890] (1866-5-30).</ref>。参议院对霍华德的提议展开了激烈的辩论，辩论主要集中在其谴辞用句上是否会比《1866年民权法案》产生更广泛的影响<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.loc.gov/law/help/citizenship/fourteenth_amendment_citizenship.php | title=Law Library of Congress: Fourteenth Amendment and Citizenship | publisher=Library of Congress | quote=The debate in the Senate was conducted in a somewhat acrimonious fashion and focused in part on the difference between the language in the definition of citizenship in the Civil Rights Act of 1866 and the proposed amendment. Specific discussion reviewed the need to address the problem created by the ''Dred Scott'' decision, but also the possibility that the language of the Howard amendment would apply in a broader fashion to almost all children born in the United States.  The specific meaning of the language of the clause was not immediately obvious. | postscript= <!-- intentionally blank to work around a bug in the template --> |accessdate=2013-12-09 |archivedate=2013-03-03 |deadurl=no |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20130303132701/http://www.loc.gov/law/help/citizenship/fourteenth_amendment_citizenship.php}}</ref>。霍华德表示这一条款“只是简单地将我看来已经成为法律的内容作一次宣示，那就是根据自然法和国家法律，所有在合众国出生或归化合众国并受其管辖的人，都是合众国的公民”<ref name="Cong_Globe_2890" />。他也补充认为公民权的赋予“当然不包括那些外交官或是受联邦政府认可的他国官员及其家人，但是应该包括所有其他层次的人。”这一补充之后将引发国会是否一开始就打算将他国人士在美国出生的后代认定为美国公民的争议。来自[[宾夕法尼亚州|宾夕法尼亚州]]的{{link-en|埃德加·科万|Edgar Cowan}}对此表示担忧，认为放宽公民权标准可能会导致一些州涌入大量不良外来移民<ref>''Cong. Globe,'' 39th Cong., 1st Sess. 2890 (1866-5-30).  "I am really desirous to have a legal definition of 'Citizenship of the United States.'  What does it mean?  What is its length and breadth? ... Is the child of the Chinese immigrant in California a citizen?  Is the child of a Gypsy born in Pennsylvania a citizen? ... Why, sir, there are nations of people with whom theft is a virtue and falsehood a merit....  It is utterly and totally impossible to mingle all the various families of men, from the lowest form of the Hottentot up to the highest Caucasian, in the same society.... and in my judgment there should be some limitation, some definition to this term 'citizen of the United States.'"</ref>；不过来自加利福尼亚州的{{link-en|约翰·康纳斯|John Conness}}则预料该州的华人总数将保持在一个很低的数字，这很大程度上是由于华人移民几乎最终总是会返回中国，而这则是因为很少会有中国的女性离开故土来到美国<ref>''Cong. Globe,'' 39th Cong., 1st Sess. 2891 (1866-5-30).</ref>。

[[威斯康星州|威斯康星州]]的{{link-en|詹姆斯·罗德·杜利特|James Rood Doolittle}}对条款表示反对，认为放宽这一限制将导致印第安人获得公民权<ref>''Cong. Globe,'' 39th Cong., 1st Sess. 2892 (1866-5-30).  "And yet by a constitutional amendment you propose to declare the Utes, the Tabahuaches, and all those wild Indians to be citizens of the United States, the great Republic of the world, whose citizenship should be a title as proud as that of king, and whose danger is that you may degrade that citizenship."</ref>，为了解决这个问题，他提议在公民权条款中增加一句民权法案的已有内容：“不包括未被征税的印第安人”<ref name="Cong_Globe_2890" />。虽然大部分参议员都同意不应该赋予印第安人公民权，但其中的大部分也认为并不必要将这个问题澄清<ref>Ho (2006), p. 372. "But although there was virtual consensus that birthright citizenship should not be extended to the children of Indian tribal members, a majority of Senators saw no need for clarification."</ref>，因此杜利特的提议经投票被否决<ref name="Cong_Globe_2897">''Cong. Globe,'' 39th Cong., 1st Sess. 2897 (1866-5-30).</ref>。修正案回到众议院时没有再引起多少辩论，也没有人对参议院增加的公民权条款表示反对，修正案于1866年6月13日在众议院投票通过<ref>''Cong. Globe,'' 39th Cong., 1st Sess. [http://memory.loc.gov/cgi-bin/ampage?collId=llcg&fileName=073/llcg073.db&recNum=270 3149] (1866-6-13).</ref>，并在1868年7月28日正式宣布通过<ref>{{cite web |title=Proclamation by William H. Seward, Secretary of State |publisher=The Library of Congress |accessdate=2013-12-09 |url=http://memory.loc.gov/cgi-bin/ampage?collId=llsl&fileName=015/llsl015.db&recNum=741 |date=1868-07-28}}</ref>。

2006年在[[加州大学伯克利分校法学院|加州大学伯克利分校法学院]]担任助理教授，并在之后成为[[加利福尼亚州最高法院|加利福尼亚州最高法院]]大法官的[[刘弘威|刘弘威]]在文章中写道，虽然公民权条款的立法历史有些“稍嫌单薄”，但其在内战后时期历史背景下的核心作用却是显而易见的<ref>{{cite journal | title=Education, Equality, and National Citizenship | author=Liu, Goodwin | journal=Yale Law Journal | year=2006 | volume=116 | page=349 | url=http://www.yalelawjournal.org/images/pdfs/393.pdf | accessdate=2013-12-09 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110706132612/http://www.yalelawjournal.org/images/pdfs/393.pdf | archivedate=2011-07-06 }}</ref>。一个名为{{le|宪法问责中心|Constitutional Accountability Center}}的[[进步主义|进步主义]][[智库|智库]]首席法律顾问伊丽莎白·威德拉（{{lang|en|Elizabeth Wydra}}）<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/elizabeth-b-wydra/ | title=Elizabeth B. Wydra |deadurl=no |archivedate=2013-03-27 |newspaper=Huffington Post | accessdate=2013-12-09 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20130327051502/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/elizabeth-b-wydra/}}</ref>认为，1866年公民权条款的支持和反对者们都认同这一条款将自动赋予所有在美国出生的人公民身份（除了外交官或入侵军队的子女）<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.acslaw.org/files/Wydra%20Issue%20Brief.pdf | title=Birthright Citizenship: A Constitutional Guarantee | author=Wydra, Elizabeth | year=2009 | publisher=American Constitution Society for Law and Policy | page=6 | accessdate=2013-12-09 | quote=For example, Senator Cowan expressed concern that the proposal would expand the number {{sic}} Chinese in California and Gypsies in his home state of Pennsylvania by granting birthright citizenship to their children, even (as he put it) the children of those who owe no allegiance to the United States and routinely commit 'trespass' within the United States.  Supporters of Howard's proposal did not respond by taking issue with Cowan's understanding, but instead by agreeing with it and defending it as a matter of sound policy. | postscript=<!-- intentionally blank to work around a bug in the template --> | archivedate=2013-07-30 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130730092241/http://www.acslaw.org/files/Wydra%20Issue%20Brief.pdf }}</ref>。[[德克萨斯州|德克萨斯州]]副检察长詹姆斯·C·胡（James C. Ho）对此也有同样的看法<ref>Ho (2006), p. 370.  "[Senator Howard's] understanding was universally adopted by other Senators.  Howard's colleagues vigorously debated the ''wisdom'' of his amendment—indeed, some opposed it precisely ''because'' they opposed extending birthright citizenship to the children of aliens of different races.  But no Senator disputed the ''meaning'' of the amendment with respect to alien children."</ref>。[[艾克朗大学|艾克朗大学]]法学院院长理查德·艾纳斯（Richard Aynes）则表示了不同看法，他认为公民权条款产生了“其制定者始料未及的效果”<ref>{{cite journal | journal=Akron Law Review | volume=39 | url=http://www.learningace.com/doc/2767615/6f351b12ed48032ca27c98041fa9aa8e/aynes392 | title=Unintended consequences of the Fourteenth Amendment and what they tell us about its interpretation | author=Aynes, Richard L. | year=2006 | page=289 | accessdate=2013-12-09 }}{{dead link|date=2018年4月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>。

=== 美国华人的公民权 ===
与其他许多国家的移民一样，华人也被吸引来了美国，起初主要是因为1849年的[[加利福尼亚淘金潮|加利福尼亚淘金潮]]，然后则是参与修建铁路、务农及在城市中找工作<ref name="Salyer" />{{rp|56}}。1868年中美两国签订《[[中美天津条约续增条约|中美天津条约续增条约]]》（又名《蒲安臣条约》），大幅扩大了中美间贸易和移民的规模<ref>[https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Burlingame_Treaty Burlingame Treaty], 16 Stat. 739.  1868-7-28.</ref>。但条约中并没有涉及两国公民在对方领土上出生子女的公民权问题<ref>{{cite web | url=http://content.cdlib.org/ark:/13030/hb4m3nb03h/?order=2&brand=calisphere | title=English and Chinese Text of the Burlingame Treaty 1868 | accessdate=2013-12-09}}</ref>。而对于[[归化|归化]]（除出生外另一个获得公民权的途径）方面，条约中包括的一条规定则是：“本条约中所包含的任何内容，不得用作归化……在美国的中国人士”<ref>{{cite journal | title=The Gestation of Birthright Citizenship, 1868–1898 States' Rights, the Law of Nations, and Mutual Consent | author=Meyler, Bernadette | journal=Georgetown Immigration Law Journal | volume=15 | pages=521–525 | year=Spring 2001}}</ref><ref>{{cite book | title=Chinese Immigrants, African Americans, and Racial Anxiety in the United States, 1848–82 | author=Aarim-Heriot, Najia | publisher=University of Illinois Press | location=Champaign, IL | pages=108–112 | isbn=0-252-02775-2}}</ref>。

很大程度上由于其完全不同文化习惯和价值观的影响，华人移民初到美国时面对的是相当普遍的不信任、不满和歧视。许多政治家认为华人实在是在太多方面存在如此巨大差異，以致于不但不会，更是不可能融入到美国的文化之中，并且还会对这个国家的原则和体制构成威胁<ref name="Salyer" />{{rp|57}}。在这种反华情绪的环境下，国会于1882年制定了《[[排华法案|排华法案]]》，对来自中国的移民作出限制<ref>[http://www.pbs.org/weta/thewest/resources/archives/seven/chinxact.htm#act An act to execute certain treaty stipulations relating to Chinese.]  47th Cong., Sess. I, Chap. 126; 22 Stat. 58.  1882-5-6.</ref>。这一法案之后还经过了数次修改<ref>{{cite journal | journal=Albany Law Journal | year=1905-9 | volume=67 | pages=259–260 | author=Dake, B. Frank | title=The Chinaman before the Supreme Court | issue=9}}</ref>，如1888年的《{{link-en|斯科特法案|Scott Act (1888)}}》<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20120909024546/http://www.uchastings.edu/racism-race/scott-act.html An act a supplement to an act entitled "An act to execute certain treaty stipulations relating to Chinese".] 50th Cong., Sess. I, Chap. 60; 25 Stat. 504.  1888-10-1.</ref>和1892年的《{{link-en|格尔瑞法案|Geary Act}}》<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20120422002348/http://www.uchastings.edu/racism-race/gearyact.html An act to prohibit the coming of Chinese persons into the United States.] 52nd Cong., Sess. I, Chap. 60; 27 Stat. 25.  1892-5-5.</ref>，这些都曾统称为《排华法案》。已经进入美国的华人可以继续生活，但他们没有资格入籍，并且當他们离开美国之后再回来時，需重新申请并获得批准。法案中还特别禁止了华人劳工和矿工进入或返回美国<ref name="ElinsonYogi" />{{rp|46}}<ref name="Chinese_Exclusion_Act">{{cite web | url=http://www.ourdocuments.gov/doc.php?flash=old&doc=47 | title=Chinese Exclusion Act (1882) | publisher=Our Documents | accessdate=2013-12-09 |archivedate=2013-10-29 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029200601/http://www.ourdocuments.gov/doc.php?flash=old&doc=47}}</ref>。

=== 法院与公民权条款 ===
在第十四条修正案通过后，黄金德案出现之前，外国人士孩童出生地公民权的问题专指华人和土著印第安人<ref>Woodworth (1896), p. 538. "It is significant that since the adoption of the Fourteenth Amendment, the question has arisen simply with reference to Chinese and Indians."</ref><ref>"Native Americans and Eskimos", 7 FAM 1117(a). "Before U.S. v. Wong Kim Ark, the only occasion on which the Supreme Court had considered the meaning of the 14th Amendment's phrase 'subject to the jurisdiction' of the United States was in Elk v. Wilkins, 112 U.S. 94 (1884)."</ref>。联邦最高法院曾在1884年的{{link-en|艾尔克诉威尔金斯案|Elk v. Wilkins}}中裁决於[[印第安保留地|保留地]]出生的印第安人不属于联邦政府管辖范围，因此不能够获得美国公民身份，亦不可因为之后只是离开保留地并放弃向之前的部落效忠就能成为美国公民<ref name="Elk">''Elk v. Wilkins'', {{ussc|112|94|1884}}.</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=Urofsky |first=Melvin I. |coauthor=Finkelman, Paul |title=A March of Liberty: A Constitutional History of the United States |edition=2nd |publisher=Oxford University Press |place=New York, NY |year=2002 |volume=1 |isbn=0-19-512635-1 |url=http://books.google.com/?id=LQVDZ9jg8m0C |accessdate=2013-09-04}}</ref>。

华人移民在美国出生的后代是否适用公民权条款的问题首先是在1884年的“陸天申案”（{{lang|en|In re Look Tin Sing}}）中提出的<ref name="look_tin_sing">''In re Look Tin Sing'', 21 F. 905 (D.Cal. 1884).  {{cite book | url=http://books.google.com/?id=CFwPAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA578&lpg=PA578&dq=%22look+tin+sing%22#v=onepage&q=%22look%20tin%20sing%22&f=false | title=Cases on constitutional law, with notes (Part 2) | author=Thayer, James Bradley | publisher=Charles W. Sever | year=1894 | pages=578–582 | accessdate=2012-01-02}}</ref>。[[陸天申|陸天申]]<ref name=xls>麥禮謙數碼檔案 [https://himmarklai.org/research-files/biographical-institutional-glossary/ English/Chinese Glossary of Biographical and Institutional Names (Excel) ] https://himmarklai.org/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/Biographical-Institutional-Glossary.xls</ref>于1870年在[[加利福尼亚州|加利福尼亚州]]{{link-en|蒙多西诺 (加利福尼亚州)|Mendocino, California|蒙多西诺}}出生，1884年他去了一趟中国，但回美国时由于不能提供当时所规定中国移民就有的足够证明文件，他被禁止入境。这个案件在[[加利福尼亚州|加利福尼亚州]]的{{link-en|美国联邦巡回法院|United States Circuit Court|联邦巡回法院}}开庭，联邦最高法院大法官{{link-en|史蒂芬·约翰逊·菲尔德|Stephen Johnson Field}}和另外两位联邦法官审理<ref name="look_tin_sing" />。据[[新罕布什爾大學|新罕布什爾大學]]历史教授露西·萨尔耶（{{lang|en|Lucy Salyer}}）<ref>{{cite web | archivedate=2013-06-22 |url=http://www.unh.edu/history/index.cfm?ID=2B1966F3-AC44-D4E7-54A916E20D9C7ED4#Salyer | title=University of New Hampshire – History Department – Faculty Profiles | accessdate=2013-06-22 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20130622135346/http://www.unh.edu/history/index.cfm?id=2B1966F3-AC44-D4E7-54A916E20D9C7ED4#Salyer}}</ref>书中所写，大法官菲尔德“向该地区所有的律师发出公开邀请，请他们就（这一案件）涉及的宪法问题发表意见”<ref name="Salyer" />{{rp|60}}。菲尔德关注于公民权条款中“并受其管辖”这一短语的含义，认为陸天申出生时，他的父母虽然是外国人士，但他仍然“受美国管辖”，因此大法官命令美国官员视陸天申为美国公民并允许他入境<ref>{{cite book | title=At America's gates:  Chinese immigration during the exclusion era, 1882–1943 | author=Lee, Erika | year=2003 | publisher=University of North Carolina Press | url=http://books.google.com/?id=BDqUb8UiCIkC&pg=PA103&lpg=PA103&dq=%22look+tin+sing%22#v=onepage&q=%22look%20tin%20sing%22&f=false | page=103 | accessdate=2012-01-02 | isbn=978-0-8078-5448-8}}</ref>。陸天申案之后并没有上诉，并且也从未被最高法院审查。1892年的另一个案件中，加利福尼亚州同一个巡回区的联邦上诉法院（即之后的[[第九巡回上诉法院|第九巡回上诉法院]]）总结认为只要一个华人可以提供足够的证据证实他是在美国境内出生的，那么就应视其为美国公民<ref>''Gee Fook Sing v. U.S.'', 49 F. 146 (9th Cir. 1892).</ref>。这一案件同样没有上诉到最高法院。

1873年，联邦最高法院在{{link-en|屠宰场案|Slaughter-House Cases}}的判决中<ref>''Slaughter-House Cases'', {{ussc|83|36|1873}}.</ref>有这样的一句表述：“‘并受其管辖’旨在排除外国领事、官员和公民在美国出生的后代”<ref name="Woodworth_1896_537" />。不过因为该案并未涉及出生公民权的问题，所以之后法院没有考虑这一表述，并视之为一个没有任何案件先例约束力的附加说明<ref name="Woodworth_1896_538" /><ref name="Semonche_1978_112" />。

